{
  "A 20 N force is applied perpendicular to a wrench 0.3 m from the bolt. What is the torque?": "",
  "6 N·m": "",
  "0.6 N·m": "",
  "60 N·m": "",
  "3 N·m": "",
  "τ = rF sinθ = 0.3 × 20 × sin 90° = 6 N·m.": "",
  "A force of 50 N is applied at 30° to a 0.4 m lever arm. What is the torque?": "",
  "10 N·m": "",
  "8 N·m": "",
  "15 N·m": "",
  "20 N·m": "",
  "τ = rF sinθ = 0.4 × 50 × sin 30° = 0.4 × 50 × 0.5 = 10 N·m.": "",
  "A disk with moment of inertia 2 kg·m² has a net torque of 10 N·m applied. What is its angular acceleration?": "",
  "0.2 rad/s²": "",
  "2 rad/s²": "",
  "5 rad/s²": "",
  "20 rad/s²": "",
  "α = τ/I = 10/2 = 5 rad/s².": "",
  "Two forces create torques of +8 N·m and −3 N·m on a pivot. What is the net torque?": "",
  "24 N·m": "",
  "5 N·m": "",
  "11 N·m": "",
  "τ_net = 8 + (−3) = 5 N·m.": "",
  "A wheel with I = 0.5 kg·m² accelerates from rest to 10 rad/s in 2 s. What net torque is applied?": "",
  "2.5 N·m": "",
  "1 N·m": "",
  "α = Δω/Δt = 10/2 = 5 rad/s². τ = Iα = 0.5 × 5 = 2.5 N·m.": "",
  "A uniform rod of mass 6 kg and length 2 m is pivoted at one end. What gravitational torque acts about the pivot? (g = 10 m/s²)": "",
  "30 N·m": "",
  "120 N·m": "",
  "12 N·m": "",
  "Gravity acts at the center (L/2 = 1 m from pivot). τ = mg(L/2) = 6 × 10 × 1 = 60 N·m.": "",
  "A torque of 12 N·m acts on a body with I = 4 kg·m² starting from rest. What is ω after 3 s?": "",
  "12 rad/s": "",
  "9 rad/s": "",
  "3 rad/s": "",
  "36 rad/s": "",
  "α = τ/I = 12/4 = 3 rad/s². ω = αt = 3 × 3 = 9 rad/s.": "",
  "A door handle is 0.8 m from the hinges. What minimum perpendicular force produces 16 N·m of torque?": "",
  "20 N": "",
  "12.8 N": "",
  "128 N": "",
  "16 N": "",
  "F = τ/r = 16/0.8 = 20 N.": "",
